          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A new measurement of 7Be(p,g)8B cross section and its",
                " astrophysical meaning"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAWAU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Tandem van de Graaff Accelerator at the",
                " University of Washington."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A monoenergetic proton beam"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A silicon surface barrier detector (alpha",
                " counting detector) with an active area of 450 mm2",
                " and a nominal thickness of 40 microm was used to",
                " count the alpha particles from the reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 7Be (from TRIUMF) was separated from lithium with",
                " a glass filter in a pH 8 - 9 solution, and left in",
                " Be0 form. Then the 7Be underwent reductive vacuum",
                " evaporation onto a catcher crucible. The target",
                " backing was made from molybdenum consisting of a flat",
                " plate with a 4 mm-diameter, 1.4 mm-height post in the",
                " center."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A calibration detector was 47.42 mm away from the",
                " target, and a 0.700 inches-diameter collimator was",
                " placed in front of the calibration detector to",
                " determine precisely the geometrical solid angle of",
                " the CY counting detector. The solid angle ratio of",
                " the counting and calibration detectors was determined",
                " with the 7Li(d,p)8Li resonance at Ed = 770 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
